author: Joseph Curtis For Mailonline
title: Floral tributes to George Michael cleared from London home | Daily Mail Online
text: Thousands of floral tributes left in honour of George Michael outside his London home are cleared away in bin liners seven weeks after the singer's death Thousands of bouquets of flowers and trinkets left outside George Michael's London home cleared away A team of workers have been spotted loading flowers into black bin bags at memorial garden in Highgate Michael, 53, was found dead at his Oxfordshire home on Christmas Day with cause of death unknown A delay in the results of toxicology tests mean his family are still unable to hold a funeral for the pop star Published: 14:37 GMT, 15 February 2017 | Updated: 15:45 GMT, 15 February 2017 32 shares
